Example 1:
Input: nums = [3,1,3,2,0]
Output: 4
Explanation:
The subarray [1, 3, 2, 0] has bitwise XOR 1 XOR 3 XOR 2 XOR 0 = 0 and contains 2 even and 2 odd numbers.

Input: nums = [3,2,8,5,4,14,9,15]
Output: 8
Explanation:
The whole array has bitwise XOR 0 and contains 4 even and 4 odd numbers.

Code--
class Solution {
    public int maxBalancedSubarray(int[] nums) {
        int maxLen = 0,even = 0,odd = 0,xor = 0;
        HashMap<String,Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        for(int i = 0;i < nums.length;i++) {
            xor ^= nums[i];
            if(nums[i] % 2 == 0) even++;
            else odd++;
            if(xor == 0 && even == odd) {
                maxLen = i + 1;
            }
            int diff = even - odd;
            String key = xor + "#" + diff;
            if(map.containsKey(key)) {
                maxLen = Math.max(maxLen,i - map.get(key));
            }else{
                map.put(key,i);
            }
        }
        return maxLen;
    }
}
